<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-09-12T18:34:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-09-12T18:34:00-05:00" n="394" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d394">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.77/475</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Chairman of the Advisory Commission of
                                    Railway Experts to Russia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SJF1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Stevens</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Harbin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-09-13T08:00:00+08:26"><hi rend="italic">September
                                            13, 1918, 8 a.m.</hi></date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 10.35 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>I have carefully examined complete records <persName corresp="#p_ECH1">Emerson</persName> acts on his western trip
                                and consider that he used excellent judgment in every case under
                                trying circumstances and I heartily approve all that he did.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed><persName corresp="#p_SJF1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Stevens</hi></persName></signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>